  "base_path": "/expenses-and-benefits-bikes-for-employees",
  "content_id": "ca724471-ab2c-4e64-9ca7-28e4da148c57",
  "description": "Tax and reporting rules for employers lending or hiring bicycles to employees",
  "details": {
    "body": "<p>As an employer, lending or hiring bikes to employees doesn’t count as an expense or benefit - as long as they’re available to all employees and mainly used for getting to work.</p>\n\n<p>This means:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you don’t have to report them to HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>you don’t deduct or pay tax and National Insurance on them</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"cycle-to-work-scheme\">Cycle to work scheme</h2>\n\n<p>You can use this to set up a <a href=\"/government/publications/cycle-to-work-scheme-implementation-guidance\">‘cycle to work’ scheme</a> to encourage employees to travel to and from work by bike.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"technical-guidance\">Technical guidance</h2>\n\n<p>The following guide contains more detailed information:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/hmrc-internal-manuals/employment-income-manual/eim21664\">particular benefits: exemption for bicycles</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n",
    "external_related_links": [

    ]
  },
  "document_type": "answer",
  "first_published_at": "2012-10-03T13:08:43Z",
